Thank you for agreeing to take part in this important survey measuring an organization's networks for innovation. In this survey, we capture opinions on individual interactions that enable innovation. This data would be used as part of a dissertation thesis to understand the factors of individual interactions that contribute to an organization's innovation. The following information is captured in this survey

1. How an individual interacts with other people with respect to idea/information exchange
2. How the organization supports social interaction and exchange of information
3. An individual's motivation to exchange idea/information
4. How the individual perceives that the idea/information exchange helps the organization to innovate

Your co-operation in completing this questionnaire is central to the success of this research project. It should take 30 minutes to complete.

You may respond with complete frankness; all your answers will remain absolutely confidential, only summary results and analysis will be published. The aggregate results produced will not make it possible to distinguish specific organizations or individuals. Individual responses, respondent’s details and the organization’s details WILL NOT be revealed.
 
Your assistance in this matter is very much appreciated. Should you have any queries, please do not hesitate to contact me.

 
I sincerely thank you for your time and participation in this study
